<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-10-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="680" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Swenson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Represent to Danish Government the great desirability of deciding at once
                            whether they will make the treaty. We cannot continue negotiations after
                            Congress meets. Ascertain whether offer of a quarter million dollars
                            more will conclude matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>